The course covers the following topics: 
1) introduction to the industrial organization; 
2) theory of economic regulation; 
3) alternative theoretical underpinnings of economic regulation; 
4) organizational innovation in the delivery of public services.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to study, using the tools of industrial economics, the optimal regulatory policies in the context of the European Union single market.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After taking the course, students will be able to * use economic theory for the analysis of the regulatory pro-competitive policies; * engage in discussions about better and innovative ways of the delivery of public services.
